| `node --expose-gc` + `global.gc()` | Force GC to isolate what's retained |
| Chrome DevTools heap snapshots | Compare two snapshots to find growing objects |
| `memwatch-next` | Emits `leak` event when heap grows 5+ consecutive GCs |

### Quick checklist

- [ ] All `EventEmitter` listeners removed when object destroyed
- [ ] No globals accumulating data unboundedly  
- [ ] All `setInterval`/`setTimeout` cleared on shutdown
- [ ] Streams properly `.destroy()`ed or `.end()`ed
- [ ] No circular references in large object graphs (though V8 handles most)

The **heap snapshot diff** approach (two snapshots minutes apart, compare "# New") is the fastest way to identify exactly what's accumulating.
